STOPOVER CHARGES: COMMON AND REGULAR FARES
Passengers may connect directly to any island without additional
charge OR passengers stopping over will pay a basic charge of
$5.40 (inc. tax) per stop-over in conjunction with circle or round trip
Common Fare routinas to or from mainland US.A. or Canada.
Passengers not traveling on Common Fare subject to regular fares.
A charge of $5.40 (inc. tax) will be made for each stop - over.
Definition of a stop-over: A stop-over is an intentional interruption
of a trin hy a nascender at a noint or noints between the cive of
departure and the furthest outbound destination.
Adult Fare: Round trip fare is twice one way fare.
Children's Fares: Two years of age and under 12, half-fare. Under
two years, free when held by parent or guardian; half-fare when
occupying reserved seat.
Early Bird and Starlighter Fares: Reduced fares in effect between
12:01 a.m. and 6:30 a.m., seven days a week, and from 8:00 p.m.
to 12:00 p.m., every night except Fridays and Sundays.
Family Plan: Available every day of the week. Full fare ticket for
one parent entitles the other parent and all children 12 through 21 to
reduced fare tickets on all flights scheduled to depart Honolulu
11 a.m. and later. and on all flights scheduled to depart neighbor
islands until 2 p.m. and on flights leaving Hilo until 4 p.m.
Senior Citizen Fare: Discount space-available to people 65 or over
who buy $5.00 membership card. Check your local HAL office for
details.
Jet Youth Plan: Discount available to those 12 through 21 years of
age on a space-available basis upon payment of $3.00 and proof
of age. Call any Hawaiian office for complete details.
Military Standby Fares: Military discount to all service personnel
on authorized leave, in uniform, on space-available basis.
Military R&R Fares: A special discount available to all personnel
and their immediate families on authorized
R&R leave. positive
space, uniform not required. Check your local HAL office for fares.
